2026-06-18  Fix (16.11, first selection after a hard refresh): the row-click handler bailed on !window.DoitPush -- which the TaskKeys hook only sets once the LiveView connects -- so on longpoll the first click(s) after a refresh were dropped entirely (no selection, no optimistic fill, nothing until a later click). Ungated it: selection + the optimistic pane fill are client-only (DoitSelection) and now run immediately; only the server pushes (select_task/close_task) are guarded on DoitPush, and the hook replays select_task for the live selection on mount so the server hydrates comments/activity/co-assignees once connected. Diagnosed + verified end-to-end over the CDP bridge in the browser.
2026-06-18  O&C (item 15.12): a viewer+ may now add themselves as a co-assignee (or primary) on their own subtree. viewer_staff_pool drew only from the nearest led ancestor co-list -- which excludes the viewer themselves (they are its primary, not a co) -- so a viewer+ could not put themselves on a descendant. It now includes the viewer in the pool for descendants of a task they lead; since the pool is the single source for both the staffing dropdowns and the server authorization (staff_pool_allows?), one change covers UI + auth. Unit tests updated.
