2026-06-18  O&C (item 15.13, supersedes 15.11.3): co-assignees now show optimistically in the pane on selection -- no "Loading..." dim. Each task row carries a hidden [data-co-seed] span per capped co-assignee; on selection fillPaneFields mirrors them into a read-only #co-optimistic list so co's appear the instant you select, before the server reply. The real interactive (reorder/remove) list still arrives on the reply and replaces the mirror; the whole real co block now hides during the in-flight switch (data-async-list on it) so its label never doubles up with the mirror's. Verified end-to-end over the CDP bridge: first selection after a hard refresh, and switches both into and out of a task with co's.
2026-06-18  Fix (item 15.14, found at gate 16.13.2): the transfer-ownership confirm dialog round-tripped before popping up -- clicking a member's transfer (key) button pushed transfer_ownership just to set @pending_transfer and re-render the modal, so the dialog waited on a server round trip (round-trip-before-input, UX_GUARDRAILS 6). Now it opens client-side like the delete confirms: the transfer button carries the target's name + id, app.js fills the copy and unhides #transfer-confirm (hidden + phx-update="ignore"), Cancel/Esc/backdrop close with no consequence, and only Proceed touches the server (confirm_transfer, carrying the stashed id). Dropped the now-dead transfer_ownership/cancel_transfer handlers and the @pending_transfer assign. Verified over the CDP bridge (cheddar/Cheese): open is synchronous with the name filled, all three close paths work, ownership untouched (never proceeded).
2026-06-19  Arc 6 +O&C 15.15 (scoped, approved): "Task creation is optimistic" -- the common add-task path round-trips before the row appears (commit_create); the completion-flip confirm path already shows an optimistic preview row, so extend that to the no-flip path -- pop the row in at submit, reconcile id/sort/roll-up on the reply, revert on failure. Roll-up % up the tree stays server-side (the noted exception). Not yet built. Backlog: new "Add Task UI" section -- Esc closes the New Task UI (exception to key suppression even when the title box is focused; discards the title, no confirm) and Up/Down reposition the add-task form's insertion point (Left/Right stay with the text cursor, so vertical-only walk through the outline with stops at both the child slot and the sibling slot).
2026-06-19  Arc 6 +O&C 15.16 (scoped, approved): "Transfer-ownership Proceed shows in-flight state." The swap is a true round trip (can't be faked optimistically), so don't close the modal as if it succeeded -- keep it open with Proceed in a working state (animate-pulse + disabled, Cancel disabled) until the server settles; confirm_transfer changes to {:reply, %{ok: ...}} so the client gets a settle signal. Repeat Proceed while in flight is dropped with the 15.9 bonk. Timeout -> swap copy to "Sorry, the transfer timed out -- try again?" and re-enable for retry. Failure (ok: false) -> helpful message + single Close, no retry (a server "no" means a precondition changed). Mirrors 15.9's undo/redo in-flight feedback, in-modal. Not yet built.
2026-06-19  Fix (15.11 follow-up, first-selection copy gap): the branch-progress copy -- "Ignored — this task has subtasks." + "Computed from children: N%" -- is server-gated on leaf-ness (invisible class on @task), so on a first selection of a branch it stayed hidden until the reply while the rest of the shell filled instantly. fillPaneFields now toggles both from the row's children presence and fills the computed readout from data-task-progress (= computed % for a branch), so the copy shows optimistically; leaves keep it hidden. CDP-verified on a true first selection (branch task 15 -> "Computed from children: 50%" instantly; leaf -> hidden).
2026-06-19  Arc 6 +O&C 15.17 (scoped, approved): "Sort menu fills optimistically." The Sort-children-by control is gated :if={@task.id} (absent on first selection) and its form/select/checkbox carry task-keyed ids, so each selection's reply rebuilds the node via morphdom and discards the optimistic value fillPaneFields wrote (verified racy across CDP runs). Fix: render it always (invisible/disabled on a blank task) + stable pane-scoped ids so morphdom updates in place; fillPaneFields fills mode/reverse/visibility from the row on every selection; SortRecall refreshes its taskId on updated() since its host stops re-mounting. Not yet built.
2026-06-19  Arc 6 item 15.15 done (optimistic task creation): the add-task form now pops a placeholder row in at submit, before the server trip -- buildPendingRow inserts an inert [data-pending-row] li (title + "Adding...", saving hue, no data-task-id so handlers skip it) into the morphdom-managed tree at the target (top level, after a sibling, or nested via a temp children-pending-<id> ul for a leaf's first child). The create reply reconciles it: success renders the real row, a completion-flip swaps in the server preview, cancel/reload drops it; an 8s timeout self-heals a dropped reply. Flip-confirm decision stays server-side (preview_create); roll-up % arrives on the reply (the exception). CDP-verified top-level/sibling/first-child-of-leaf, each reconciling with no ghost; test tasks cleaned up.
2026-06-19  Arc 6 item 15.16 done (transfer-ownership Proceed in-flight state): the swap can't be optimistic, so the confirm modal no longer closes on Proceed -- it holds open with Proceed pulsing ("Transferring...", animate-pulse, kept clickable so a repeat bonks) and Cancel disabled until the reply. confirm_transfer now returns {:reply, %{ok: bool}}: ok -> close; ok:false -> body swaps to a helpful "membership may have changed" message with a single Close, no retry; an 8s timeout swaps to "Sorry, the transfer timed out -- try again?" and re-enables Proceed. A repeat Proceed mid-flight is dropped with window.DoitBonk (exposed from the TaskKeys hook). CDP-verified working/failure/close/reset over the bridge with a bogus id (no real transfer); Cheese ownership untouched.
2026-06-19  Arc 6 item 15.17 done (sort menu fills optimistically): the task-pane sort control now renders always (dropped :if={@task.id}; a blank task renders it invisible) so it's present on a first selection, and the form/select/checkbox carry stable pane-scoped ids (scope="task"/"init") instead of task-keyed ones, so morphdom updates them in place and the optimistic value survives + reconciles rather than being torn down. fillPaneFields fills mode/reverse/visibility and points the form's hidden task_id + data-task-id at the selected task on every selection; SortRecall refreshes its taskId on updated() since its host no longer re-mounts. CDP-verified: the menu now appears + fills on first selection, and at normal pace mode/reverse load on every subsequent selection. Known pre-existing edge (not a regression, broader than sort): under rapid-fire selection where replies lag behind clicks, fillPaneFields can be skipped when the pane momentarily reads as already-arrived -- not hit at human pace.
